Unknown gunmen have killed a Fulani leader, Alhaji Abdullahi Hardo Buruku popularly known as Alhaji Malam, in Lamba town, Asa local government area of Kwara state. A resident of Lamba told Daily Trust that the gunmen stormed the town around 12mid night on Wednesday, shooting in the air. “They shot him on the spot. We heard  gunshots all over,” he said. Also one of the sisters of the deceased, Aina’u Hardo Buruku, confirmed the incident to Daily Trust. She said the gunmen met the victim in his bedroom and murdered him. Until his death, the  deceased was the chairman, Gan Allah  Fulani Development Association of Nigeria, Kwara  state branch. He was the eldest son of the late Sarkin Fulani of Kwara, Alhaji Mu’azu Hardo Buruku.